cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with wireless body area networks (WBANs) and proposes a distributed scheme for interference mitigation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses simulations, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
